## 📝 GitHub Story #3 — Don't Sell Technology

One mistake became obvious during our own testing.

We spent too much time talking about **how** my side project worked.

The database.

The indicators.

The architecture.

The code.

Then we looked at it again.

None of those things actually mattered.

What mattered was one simple question.

> "Can this help me make a better decision?"

That changed how we built every new feature after that.

Instead of asking,

> "Is this technically interesting?"

we started asking,

> "Would anyone actually care?"
